<!-- Fn::Join -->
<section id="intrinsic-function-reference-join" role="topic">
   <title id="intrinsic-function-reference-join.title">Fn::Join</title>
   
   <para>The intrinsic function <function>Fn::Join</function> appends a set of values into a single value, separated
      by the specified delimiter. If a delimiter is the empty string, the set of values are concatenated with no
      delimiter.</para>

   <section>
      <title>Declaration</title>
      <para>"Fn::Join" : [ "<parameter>delimiter</parameter>", [ <replaceable>comma-delimited list of
         values</replaceable> ] ]</para>
   </section>

   <section>
      <title>Parameters</title>
      <variablelist>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>delimiter</term>
            <listitem>
               <simpara>The value you want to occur between fragments. The delimiter will occur between fragments only. It
                  will not terminate the final value.</simpara>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
         <varlistentry>
            <term>listOfValues</term>
            <listitem>
               <simpara>The list of values you want combined.</simpara>               
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
   </section>

   <section>
      <title>Return Value</title><para>The combined string.</para>
   </section>

   <section>
      <title>Example</title>
      <programlisting format="linespecific">"Fn::Join" : [ ":", [ "a", "b", "c" ] ]</programlisting>
      <para>This example returns: <returnvalue>"a:b:c"</returnvalue>.</para>
   </section>
</section>

